---
/**
 * context-engineering 0004 · Figure 3 — "five ways context breaks".
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from
 * docs/context-engineering/lessons/0004-memory-compression-and-failure-modes.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption incl. the footnote <sup id="r3">). Lives as an
 * .astro component for the same reason as Fig1/Fig2: raw inline SVG with
 * kebab-case attributes is unreliable inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 *
 * The markers this figure references (arwR, arw) are inlined into its own
 * <defs> — the source page defined them once in a shared <body> <defs> block.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 640 250"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Five ways context breaks: missing, wrong, outdated, conflicting, and excessive context, each producing a bad answer."
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwR"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#9a2417"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <text x="320" y="18" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#111110"
            >Five ways context breaks</text
        >
        <!-- five sources -->
        <rect
            x="20"
            y="34"
            width="116"
            height="58"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="78" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Missing</text
        >
        <text x="78" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">never retrieved</text>
        <text x="78" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">"I don't know"</text>

        <rect
            x="148"
            y="34"
            width="116"
            height="58"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="206" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Wrong</text
        >
        <text x="206" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >irrelevant pulled</text
        >
        <text x="206" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">confident, off</text>

        <rect
            x="276"
            y="34"
            width="116"
            height="58"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="334" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Outdated</text
        >
        <text x="334" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >stale index/cache</text
        >
        <text x="334" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">old price/API</text>

        <rect
            x="404"
            y="34"
            width="116"
            height="58"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="462" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Conflicting</text
        >
        <text x="462" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >sources disagree</text
        >
        <text x="462" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">contradictory</text>

        <rect
            x="532"
            y="34"
            width="108"
            height="58"
            rx="8"
            fill="#fbecec"
            stroke="#9a2417"
            stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
        <text x="586" y="56" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#9a2417"
            >Excessive</text
        >
        <text x="586" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">too much packed</text
        >
        <text x="586" y="84" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">lost in middle</text>

        <!-- arrows down -->
        <line x1="78" y1="92" x2="220" y2="138" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="206" y1="92" x2="280" y2="138" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="334" y1="92" x2="334" y2="138" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="462" y1="92" x2="388" y2="138" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>
        <line x1="586" y1="92" x2="448" y2="138" stroke="#9a2417" marker-end="url(#arwR)"></line>

        <!-- bad answer -->
        <rect
            x="200"
            y="140"
            width="240"
            height="40"
            rx="9"
            fill="#f1eef2"
            stroke="#b5179e"
            stroke-width="1.8"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="160" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" font-weight="700" fill="#b5179e"
            >Same LLM &mdash; bad answer</text
        >
        <text x="320" y="174" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
            >not the model's fault: the window was wrong</text
        >

        <line x1="320" y1="180" x2="320" y2="206" stroke="#6b675f" marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
        <rect x="170" y="208" width="300" height="32" rx="8" fill="#e9f3ec" stroke="#2f5d3a"></rect>
        <text x="320" y="228" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" font-weight="700" fill="#2f5d3a"
            >Classify the shape &rarr; the fix is obvious</text
        >
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        All five funnel into the same symptom — a bad answer from a fine model. The diagnostic skill
        is sorting <em>which</em> shape it is; the table below maps each to its root cause and fix.<sup
            ><a href="#s3" id="r3">3</a></sup
        >
    </figcaption>
</figure>
